				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">1 an upgraded ae mez , possible a targeted , pbae that maxes at the highest lvl we can mez</span>
<br />

<br />
If its PBAE, its a WOM upgrade. If its targeted AE, it will be a WOF (wake of Euphoria?). <span style="font-style: italic">I would like the WOM upgrade please.</span> Use of targeted AE mez spells (especially WOF and any possible upgrade to it) is fairly suicidal given the fact that mobs at that level (70 and above) hit like mack trucks on resistance aggro. Without a negative resist and aggro adjustment, targeted AE spells cannot be in the top 10 of any list. 
<br />

<br />
Go with the WOM upgrade idea.  
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">2 bring back our single target stuns . so instead of us relying on a mez or a pbae stun , we can use a single target .</span>
<br />

<br />
Sounds nice but I shudder at the possible implementation. Really.
<br />
Why were our single target stuns (L16 "whirl till you hurl" etc.) nerfed in the first place (wow 6 years ago!)? Because we could chain a tashed stun mob for just about forever while it gets beaten. Verant (!) nerfed that by having the stun break almost instaneously. No, not like root - root breaks randomly with more than 50% lasting the whole listed duration  - our targeted stuns don't last anything like the 6 seconds (or whatever) listed. They last for 1 second 99% of the time.
<br />

<br />
So lets say they give us back targeted stun.
<br />

<br />
Aggro - without a huge negative aggro adjustment (I mean GINORMOUS negative aggro adjustment) - we become silk armored paladins.
<br />
Resist and stun duration - if these new targeted stuns are anything like the old ones - just being higher level - well no-one is going to use them. Why waste all that mana for a stun (that will aggro) that will last probably 1 second 99% of the time. Ditto on the resist rate (paladins dont mind the resist - they just want the aggro, the stunnage is a bonus).
<br />

<br />
Nice idea - but high probability of SOE FUBAR job 
<br />
Near certainty in fact - cynical yet realistic, sorry.
<br />
In all honesty, I predict this stun (if it gets implemented at all), will be DOA to the chanter community given SOE's track record when it comes to this sort of stuff.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">3 new rapture type mez would be really nice too .</span>
<br />
Nice; but like previous rapture spells, not something we trot out in 99% of our gameplay. Its pretty specialized to be put into a TOP 10 list ennit? Better idea - why not just reduce the recast time for stasis? ref below.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">4 maybe reduce aa reuse timers on Mind over matter , soothing words , stasis</span>
<br />
Nice... I guess.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Quellious Cold Fury</span>
<br />
Greif 70 Coercer Chanter
