			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Mezzes are already lower resist than pretty much any stun in the game.  If we can land a mez, we don't have problems.
<br />

<br />
What enchanters need is more options when the mez is resisted.  These options need to be viable both in easy content, where a tank and healer can deal with 2 mobs at once, and in hard content, where healers have problems chain-healing and keeping tanks up if the mob is unslowed.
<br />

<br />
In-camp crowd control used to be a viable specialization.  A number of things has made it obsolete.
<br />

<br />
1&gt; PlateTank:SilkCaster durability ratios.  Plate classes tank so much better nowadays it isn't funny.
<br />
2&gt; DPS-centered reward model.
<br />
3&gt; Lack of defensive spells.  Enchanters now have <span style="font-weight: bold">one fast casting defence spell</span>, and that one takes 2 seconds to cast.  We used to have 4 or more, with multples with casting times from 1.0 to 1.5.
<br />
4&gt; More powerful pull abilities.
<br />
5&gt; Content set up to be single-pulled almost all of the time.
<br />

<br />
Of the above, I think 2 and 4 shouldn't be changed.  DPS-centered reward is better than the old camp-time reward.  And the pull abilities should be giving players an alternative to in-camp crowd control.
<br />

<br />
For ponit 1, I agree in general, but not for the enchanter class in particular.  We need more durability to do our jobs.
<br />

<br />
Number 3 is a god damn crime.  SOE has stripped enchanter defensive spells one at a time, until we are basically gimped with mobs attacking us.  In exchange, we have gotten long-reuse AA abilities that usually just make the mob attack someone else in our party.  <span style="font-weight: bold">If the group can't handle 2 mobs without the enchanter, when the enchanter makes the mob attack a random member of the party, the party loses</span>.  Aggro-dump abilities are not defensive abilities against uncontrolled adds, they are a recipie for party-wipe.
<br />

<br />
I think the top-10 list already has a request to redo #3, and add more defensive spells?
<br />

<br />
But basically, enchanters need more <span style="font-weight: bold">truely defensive</span> options for when we get a resist.  A resist on challenging content should be expensive, not party-fatal.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
