			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I agree with Yakk, that we need either our defensive skills backs, spells, defensive AAs with shorter re-use times, and improved avoidance or mitigation.
<br />

<br />
However, as long as mobs hit like Mack tracks, unless the rest of the classes get such a boost, the single pulling focus will not go away, and everyone will camp stuff that can be saefly singled. Thus, even if we get Monk-like avoidance AND Warrior-like DMG mitigation, it will have little effect. SoE will not design zones with in-camp crowd control since then chantercy would be required for groups again, unless they do expand those abilities to all classes.
<br />

<br />
From what I have read lately, the option that I like best is the sugestion of progressive mob DPS, hitting harder as they take DMG (i.e. 50% of total DPS when between 90% and 100% HPs left, and normal DPS when under 90%). That would allow for more in-camp add control, without requiring an enchanter. And while 5+ adds would still most likely wipe group, 1 or 2 adds could be offtanked, pet ghetto mezzed, or even root parked if no mezzer in group. Only then, SoE could start pondering the posibilities of roamers in high end zones, which IMO enhance everyones fun factor.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
