			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Manizeh wrote: " Only then, SoE could start pondering the posibilities of roamers in high end zones, which IMO enhance everyones fun factor."
<br />

<br />
Actually, I would like to see more zones where the npc's actually looked like they were busy doing things in normal life.  There should be monsters runing errands for other monsters, doing things, conducting business, etc.   We enter a cave with slaves in a mine for example, the just stay there at their job, not moving, the guards stay there not moving and nobody does anything. How realistic is that?  
<br />

<br />
We need wandering mobs that have missions, places to go, things to do, monsters to see.  Zones that are static when you enter them with all the mobs standing in thier one spot forever are really unrealistic, and it really makes you feel like you are in a game.   Role playing should be a little more dynamic and realistic.  This is a "role-playing" game...right?   <img src="images/smiles/eusa_doh.gif" alt="d'oh!" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Also, the mobs could do some of the things we do, to make them seem more intelligent.  For example, we enter a mission and attack the first mob:
<br />

<br />
Mob 1: /ooc I have intruders at Zone-in, I am engaging them in combat now.
<br />

<br />
Boss mob deep in: /ooc Very good mob 1, report when you have vanquished them.
<br />

<br />
Mob 1: /ooc Oh no! they are too strong..i perish now!
<br />

<br />
Boss mob: /ooc Mob 1 has been slain, all minions be on the lookout for the intruders. Scouts start to look. 
<br />

<br />
Scout 1: /ooc I found them at loc #, #, # I need back-up....AAAAAAAAHHHHH.... 
<br />

<br />
Scout 2: /ooc They got my brother Scout 1, I will have my revenge!
<br />

<br />
Boss mob: /ooc Mob 2, 3 and 4 head to that loc immediately and kill the intruders.  Mobs 4, 5 and 6, fall back to the bridge and fortify your positions.  
<br />

<br />
Then the mobs coordinate their attacks, the groups get ready for a small train or they run and get out of the area so the mobs can't find them and it would seem much more realistic. DON does have some of these type things, and I hope SOE does more of them. 
<br />

<br />
Lillywhite</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
