			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I stand corrected, it should be "shout" not /ooc. 
<br />

<br />
Yes it will take coding, and there would have to be numerous different responses depending on what you did.
<br />

<br />
My point was that if they had a better Artificial Intelligence(AI), where the mobs would reasonably act like they had things to do, and respond in ways similar to the way we might when confronted, then SOE would not need to just rely on Dumb mobs standing there with their 2 million hp's doing nothing for eternity except waiting for  somone to walk up and attack them so they can quad for 2k damage / sec.  Massive damage single mobs would not be needed if the mobs could use abilities in a coordinated way. Instead of having mobs only agro by proximity, they should be able to shout for help indicating thier loc, and either have other mobs shout back they are coming, or have the boss shout orders directing them etc. The group would prepare itself, the mobs would come at different times depending on how far they were away at the time orders were given, and the group would expect an assortment of cleric and caster types helping each other.  It would sort of be more a group of players vrs a zone of raid of players except the raid would be all npc's with a very high Artificial intelligence, constrained by the role-play personalities that were given to the boss mobs and follower mobs. 
<br />

<br />
I would like to see mobs that were more powerful because they were more intelligent, rather than just keep increasing the damage and hit points they have.  It would make the game more interesting, fun, dynamic and less stagnent.  
<br />

<br />
If the next expansion had new zones and mobs desigened with a new and different AI, I believe it would be a great advetizing thing for SOE, many people would return to try it out and it would breath new life into the old game. 
<br />

<br />
Lillywhite</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
